High-Level Architecture:

API Gateway → Inventory Service → MongoDB
      ↓              ↓
   Redis Cache    RabbitMQ → Stock Update Workers
      ↓
   Monitoring (Prometheus + Grafana)

Component Interaction:

HTTP requests hit API Gateway

Auth middleware validates JWT tokens

Controllers handle routing

Services implement business logic with caching

Stock updates publish to RabbitMQ for async processing

MongoDB for persistence, Redis for caching

Folder Structure:

inventory-sync-api/
├── src/
│   ├── modules/
│   │   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── inventory/
│   │   ├── products/
│   │   ├── warehouses/
│   │   └── webhooks/
│   ├── common/
│   │   ├── decorators/
│   │   ├── filters/
│   │   ├── guards/
│   │   ├── interceptors/
│   │   └── middleware/
│   ├── config/
│   ├── queue/
│   └── utils/
├── tests/
├── docker/
└── docs/

Core Features
JWT Authentication & API Key Management

Real-time Stock Synchronization across channels

Reservation System to prevent overselling

Webhook Support for external integrations

Distributed Caching with Redis

Event-driven Architecture with RabbitMQ

Rate Limiting and request throttling

Comprehensive Logging and monitoring
